From our app, we had a custom JacksonBuilder to avoid NULL values.
So we had to specify those properties inside our custom mapper. And not in the application.properties file
```
@SpringBootApplication
public class JavaConnecteurESApplication {
public static void main(String[] args) {
    SpringApplication.run(JavaConnecteurESApplication.class, args);
}

@Bean
public Jackson2ObjectMapperBuilder objectMapperBuilder() {
    Jackson2ObjectMapperBuilder builder = new Jackson2ObjectMapperBuilder();
    builder.serializationInclusion(JsonInclude.Include.NON_NULL);
        // This line below is the magic one for me. Obviously, if need to switch properties to true, use featuresToEnable 
    builder.featuresToDisable(SerializationFeature.WRITE_DATE_TIMESTAMPS_AS_NANOSECONDS);
